<task id="050" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend ChatEndpoints to accept attachments[] payload (FR-07 backend half) — CONDITIONAL</title>
    <phase>Phase E — Backend (conditional on spike 001 outcome)</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>051</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api, endpoints, ai, conditional</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies the BFF `Sprk.Bff.Api` ChatEndpoints — a load-bearing C# endpoint definition. Per CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene, any addition to `Sprk.Bff.Api` requires explicit placement justification + ADR-013 compliance. ADR-008 endpoint-filter inheritance must be preserved. Single-LLM-call invariant (D-01) must be preserved. FULL rigor with Step 9.5 code-review + adr-check.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Pairs with task 051 (tests). Different files; both can be drafted concurrently in the same wave, though 051 verification depends on 050 build being green.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    ONLY EXECUTE if task 001 spike result determined the chat endpoint requires server-side
    extension to accept attachments[]. If the spike concluded "client-side extraction only,
    no BFF changes required," mark this task SKIPPED in TASK-INDEX.md and stop.

    Extend the BFF chat endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/messages` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` to accept an optional
    `attachments: Array&lt;{filename, contentType, textContent}&gt;` field on the request DTO.
    Validate the payload, pass the attachment text into the existing single LLM call's
    context, and preserve the single-LLM-call invariant (D-01). All existing endpoint
    filters (auth, rate limit, validation, problem-details) inherit per ADR-008. No new
    feature module or DI registration is created (ADR-013 — extend BFF in-process).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 backend developer experienced with Minimal API endpoint definitions in
    Sprk.Bff.Api. Familiar with ADR-008 endpoint-filter inheritance, ADR-013 AI architecture
    (in-process extension, no new service), and the single-LLM-call invariant D-01 enforced
    by AnalysisOrchestrationService / chat orchestrator. Comfortable working in the
    `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade boundary established by the 2026-05-20 BFF AI
    extraction assessment.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ChatEndpoints.cs` accepts an optional `Attachments` list on the message-send request DTO,
    validated for: max 5 entries (additional rejected with 400), max 10 MB per textContent
    field (NFR-04), and contentType in the allow-list (`text/plain`, `text/markdown`,
    `application/pdf`,
    `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document`). Disallowed
    MIME types are rejected with 400 + problem-details. The validated attachment text is
    appended to the single existing LLM call's user-message context — there is still exactly
    ONE LLM call per user turn. Existing endpoint filters (auth, rate limit) continue to
    fire on the modified endpoint. Build succeeds with no new warnings; no new CVE; no new
    NuGet packages introduced.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-07 enables multi-file attachments in the Assistant input strip. Task 001 (the spike)
      determined whether attachment text extraction stays purely client-side (PDF.js +
      mammoth before chat send) or whether the BFF endpoint also needs to accept the
      extracted text in its message payload. If the spike concluded the latter, this task
      wires the request DTO. Per ADR-013 + CLAUDE.md §10, this is an in-process extension
      of an existing endpoint — no new feature module, no new DI registration.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/spikes/fr07-attachments-spike-result.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">All existing endpoint filters (auth, rate-limit, validation, problem-details) MUST continue to fire on the modified endpoint. Do not bypass the filter pipeline. Validation errors return RFC 7807 problem-details.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">This is an in-process extension of an existing BFF endpoint, not a new service. No new feature module, no new DI registration in `Program.cs`. Do not inject `IOpenAiClient` or other AI-internal types directly — use the existing chat orchestration path already wired through the endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — no new DI registrations. Reuse the existing chat services already injected by the endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Validation failures return RFC 7807 problem-details, not bespoke error shapes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Endpoint auth continues to be enforced by existing endpoint filters; no token snapshotting; do not introduce new auth code paths.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">D-01 single-LLM-call invariant — attachment text is appended to the SAME LLM call's user-message context. Do NOT trigger a separate LLM call for extraction or summary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-04 — max 10 MB per attachment textContent; max 5 attachments per message.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Allowed MIME types: `text/plain`, `text/markdown`, `application/pdf`, `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document`. Reject all others with 400 + problem-details.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions">Per CLAUDE.md §10 + `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`: extension is in-place on an existing endpoint, with NO new packages. Verify `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` reports no new HIGH-severity CVE. Verify publish size is unchanged (no new NuGet refs added).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CONDITIONAL: if spike 001 concluded BFF extension is NOT needed, mark this task SKIPPED and do not proceed.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
