  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Verify spike 001 outcome">
      Read `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/spikes/fr07-attachments-spike-result.md`
      (or the equivalent spike result memo). Confirm the recommendation is "extend BFF endpoint."
      If the recommendation is "client-side only," mark this task SKIPPED in TASK-INDEX.md and
      stop. Do not proceed with code changes.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read existing ChatEndpoints + DTO">
      Open `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs`. Identify the `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/messages`
      handler and the request DTO it binds (likely `SendMessageRequest` or similar). Note the
      existing endpoint filter chain registered on this endpoint group.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Add Attachments to request DTO">
      Add an optional `IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatAttachmentDto&gt; Attachments` property (or
      equivalent) to the request DTO. Define `ChatAttachmentDto` with three fields:
      `Filename` (string), `ContentType` (string), `TextContent` (string). Default to empty
      list when absent. Place the DTO alongside the existing request DTO in the same file
      or a sibling DTOs file — keep the change minimal.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement validation rules">
      Inside the handler (before invoking the chat orchestration path), validate:
      <list>
        <item>`Attachments.Count &lt;= 5` → otherwise return 400 ProblemDetails with title "Too many attachments."</item>
        <item>Each `TextContent.Length &lt;= 10 * 1024 * 1024` (10 MB UTF-16; use a const) → otherwise 400 ProblemDetails.</item>
        <item>Each `ContentType` is in the allow-list (`text/plain`, `text/markdown`, `application/pdf`, `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document`) → otherwise 400 ProblemDetails listing the rejected type.</item>
      </list>
      Use existing `Results.Problem(...)` helpers consistent with ADR-019.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Pass attachments into single LLM call context">
      Append the validated attachment text into the SAME user-message context that already
      feeds the existing chat orchestration call. Use a simple, deterministic concatenation
      format (e.g., `--- Attachment: {filename} ({contentType}) ---\n{textContent}\n`) so the
      LLM has clear file boundaries. Do NOT introduce a separate LLM call for extraction or
      summary — the single-LLM-call invariant D-01 is non-negotiable.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify endpoint filter inheritance">
      Confirm the existing endpoint filter chain (auth filter, rate-limit filter, validation
      filter, problem-details filter) still applies to the modified handler. No filter should
      be moved or removed. Add an inline comment near the handler header noting filter
      inheritance per ADR-008.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build BFF + verify no new warnings">
      Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify zero new compiler warnings.
      Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` and verify no NEW
      HIGH-severity CVE versus the pre-change baseline.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Optional: smoke against running BFF">
      If a local BFF is running, send a sample request with 0, 1, and 5 attachments through
      curl/Postman; confirm 200 OK with attachment text reflected in the model response, and
      400 on 6+ / oversized / disallowed-MIME variants.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read existing ChatEndpoints.cs, spike result, DTO files</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Modify ChatEndpoints.cs + DTO</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Locate existing endpoint filter registration, RFC 7807 helpers</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`; `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</output>
    <output type="code">DTO for ChatAttachmentDto (inline or sibling file)</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report confirming endpoint accepts validated attachments[], single-LLM-call invariant preserved, all endpoint filters still apply</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Spike 001 outcome was verified before proceeding; if outcome was "client-side only," this task is marked SKIPPED.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Request DTO accepts optional `Attachments: ChatAttachmentDto[]` field with `Filename`, `ContentType`, `TextContent`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Request with 1, 3, or 5 attachments is accepted; 6+ is rejected with 400 RFC 7807 problem-details.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`TextContent` &gt; 10 MB is rejected with 400 RFC 7807 problem-details.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ContentType` outside the allow-list is rejected with 400 RFC 7807 problem-details.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Validated attachment text is appended to the existing SINGLE LLM call's user-message context — no second LLM call is introduced (D-01 preserved).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All existing endpoint filters (auth, rate limit, validation, problem-details) continue to apply per ADR-008.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` succeeds with zero new warnings; `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` reports no new HIGH-severity CVE; no new NuGet packages added.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

